# Meavo style guide

Official reference: https://meavo.com/style-guide (PDF: MEAVO Style Guide)

Use this for typography, palette, spacing, and visual tone when building or updating Meavo UI (gateway, hols, and related apps).

## App button greens (do not change)

Primary buttons in the apps intentionally use these values — **keep them even if the PDF shows other greens**:

- Default: `#30A46C` (`brand-600`)
- Hover: `#0C8F61` (`brand-700`)

Defined in `tailwind.config.ts` as `bg-brand-600` / `hover:bg-brand-700`.

## Brand palette (from style guide)

| Token | Hex | Use |
|-------|-----|-----|
| Near black | `#212121` | Primary text |
| Mid grey | `#727272` | Secondary text |
| Light grey | `#EAEAEA` | Borders, dividers |
| Warm white | `#FAF9F7` | Page backgrounds |
| Cream | `#F2F0EB` | Cards, panels |
| Warm beige | `#ECE8E1` | Subtle fills |
| Greige | `#D7D3CD` | Muted accents |
| Cool tint | `#E1E9EC` | Secondary surfaces |
| Blush | `#EEDCDC` | Soft accent |
| Gold | `#F4E3B1` | Highlight accent |

## UI conventions (apps)

- Neutral structure: `slate-*` for borders, nav, and form chrome (already in use).
- Cards: white background, `rounded-xl`, light border, soft shadow.
- Focus rings: `brand-100` / `brand-500` on inputs.
- Logo: `/meavo-logo.png` — do not substitute text-only branding on login or nav.

When adding new UI, align with the guide’s warm, minimal, professional tone. Prefer the palette above over ad-hoc colors.
